This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with obstacle detection and tracking in real-world scenes. The use of automated vehicles also suggests a potential application in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology proposed in the paper involves the use of sensors and data analysis, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the precision metrics and error analysis presented in the paper suggest a potential application in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
